    "updated_at": "2015-05-04T19:31:20Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Ok, but right now as far as I understand it's not possible to plug in external backend to ipython since it requires to add it to hardcoded \"backends\" constant here \nhttps://github.com/ipython/ipython/blob/master/IPython/core/pylabtools.py\n\nWhat I do right now (in Installation section in README https://github.com/oselivanov/matplotlib_iterm2) - I do monkey patching of this \"backends\" constant (and some other one) in ipython user profile to bypass ipython checks. It works, but it's really dirty.\n\nIs there a way to make ipython see external backends?\n"
  },
